                <p><pb n="7"/><hi rend="italic">Extract of a letter from a gentleman at Dumfries, <lb/>in Virginia, to his correspondent in Glasgow, <lb/>dated 3d October, 1789.</hi></p>
                <p>"Yesterday morning we had a frost, by which <lb/>a very considerable part of the growing tobacco, <lb/>twenty miles from the rivers, was killed, then the <lb/>Mercury was at 35 to a northern exposure in the <lb/>open air; this morning it stood at 27, and every <lb/>tender vegetable in the gardens here is destory<lb break="no"/>ed."</p>
